    • initChannel

      protected void initChannel(C ch) throws Exception
      This method will be called once the Channel was registered. After the method returns this instance will be removed from the ChannelPipeline of the Channel.
      Specified by:
      initChannel in class ChannelInitializer<C extends io.netty.channel.Channel>
      Parameters:
      ch - the Channel which was registered.
      Throws:
      Exception - is thrown if an error occurs. In that case it will be handled by ChannelInitializer.exceptionCaught(io.netty.channel.ChannelHandlerContext, Throwable) which will by default close the Channel.
